Everything You Need to Know

FAQs

Patients and professionals often have concerns about alternative medicine, ketamine therapy, and medical cannabis. Here are the answers to some of the most common questions to help you make an informed decision about your health.

Is ketamine therapy covered by insurance?
Currently, ketamine therapy is not covered by most insurance providers. However, many patients find that the benefits far outweigh the costs, and financing options may be available.
How does medical cannabis work for mental health?
Medical cannabis interacts with the body’s endocannabinoid system, helping regulate mood, pain, and inflammation. It has been shown to provide relief for anxiety, PTSD, and chronic pain.
Who qualifies for ketamine or medical cannabis treatment?
Patients with chronic pain, treatment-resistant depression, PTSD, anxiety, and other qualifying conditions may be eligible. Each case is evaluated individually to determine the best course of treatment.
Are these treatments safe?
Yes. Under the supervision of a qualified physician like Dr. Rosado, ketamine therapy and medical cannabis are both scientifically validated and used in clinical settings worldwide.
How quickly do these treatments work?
Ketamine therapy can produce results within hours to days, providing relief even for patients who have struggled with depression for years.

Medical cannabis effects depend on the condition being treated and the method of consumption but can provide immediate to gradual relief.
What’s the first step if I want to start treatment?
The first step is booking a consultation with Dr. Rosado. During this session, you’ll discuss your health concerns and receive a personalized treatment plan tailored to your needs
What makes Dr. Rosado’s treatment approach different for chronic pain, mental health, and neurological disorders?
If standard treatments worked for everyone, you wouldn’t be here looking for answers.

The reality is, many people battling chronic pain, mental health challenges, and neurological disorders don’t find relief with traditional medications. Dr. Joseph Rosado offers a different approach—personalized, science-backed treatment plans that harness your body’s natural ability to heal.
